Class JavaList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>

          • genius.core.list.JavaList<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class JavaList<E>
extends java.util.ArrayList<E>
    Adapts ImmutableList to java.util.List. But it stays immutable. Supports quick adapter to old code. fetches all items from the old list. Try to avoid this and use ImmutableList all the way.
